<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="a17Mar1939"><font color="red">17 March 1939</font> <i>NLHW</i> (from Paul L&eacute;on to Harriet Weaver): I beg to be excused for not having warned that the rest of the sheets and proofs was to be taken by my wife but she made up her mind on the trip without any warning and it was the easiest way to take them over &hellip; I enclose herewith a cutting from the Paris New York Herald about Mr Joyce&apos;s agent who absconded with some royalties. </div>
